### 4. Content Blocks

ContentBlock is a tagged union using MCP's content block format:

```json
// Text
{"type": "text", "text": "Hello world"}

// Image (requires image prompt capability)
{"type": "image", "mimeType": "image/png", "data": "<base64>"}

// Audio (requires audio prompt capability)
{"type": "audio", "mimeType": "audio/wav", "data": "<base64>"}

// Embedded text resource (requires embeddedContext capability)
{"type": "resource", "resource": {"uri": "file:///path", "mimeType": "text/x-python", "text": "..."}}

// Embedded blob resource
{"type": "resource", "resource": {"uri": "file:///path", "mimeType": "application/pdf", "blob": "<base64>"}}

// Resource link (always supported)
{"type": "resource_link", "uri": "file:///path", "name": "document.pdf", "mimeType": "application/pdf", "size": 1024000}
```

**Tool call content** (in `tool_call` / `tool_call_update` content arrays) has three types:
```json
// Regular content wrapping a ContentBlock
{"type": "content", "content": {"type": "text", "text": "..."}}

// Diff (file edit)
{"type": "diff", "path": "/abs/path", "oldText": "...", "newText": "..."}

// Terminal reference
{"type": "terminal", "terminalId": "term_001"}
```

### 5. ToolCall Object Shape (all fields)

```
ToolCall {
  toolCallId: string          (required) - Unique ID within session
  title: string               (required) - Human-readable description
  kind?: ToolKind             - "read"|"edit"|"delete"|"move"|"search"|"execute"|"think"|"fetch"|"switch_mode"|"other"
  status?: ToolCallStatus     - "pending"|"in_progress"|"completed"|"failed"
  content?: ToolCallContent[] - Array of {type:"content",...}|{type:"diff",...}|{type:"terminal",...}
  locations?: [{path:string, line?:number}]  - File locations affected
  rawInput?: any              - Raw tool input parameters
  rawOutput?: any             - Raw tool output
  _meta?: object              - Extension metadata
}
```

`ToolCallStart` extends `ToolCall` with `sessionUpdate: "tool_call"`.
`ToolCallProgress` (updates) extends `ToolCallUpdate` with `sessionUpdate: "tool_call_update"`. In updates, only `toolCallId` is required; all other fields are optional (send only what changed).

### 6. Session State/History

Yes, via `session/load`. When a client calls:
```json
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"session/load","params":{"sessionId":"sess_789xyz","cwd":"/path","mcpServers":[]}}
```

The agent replays the entire conversation history as a stream of `session/update` notifications (`user_message_chunk`, `agent_message_chunk`, `tool_call`, `tool_call_update`, etc.), then responds with `{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"result":null}`.

There is also `session/list` (unstable/draft, in `sessionCapabilities`) which returns session metadata:
```json
{"sessions": [{"sessionId":"...", "cwd":"...", "title":"...", "updatedAt":"2025-..."}]}
```

Additional session methods (in draft/unstable): `session/fork`, `session/resume`, `session/close`.

### 7. The ACP Wrapper (`claude-agent-acp`)

**Package**: Originally `@zed-industries/claude-code-acp`, now renamed to `@agentclientprotocol/claude-agent-acp`.

**What it does**: It is an ACP-compatible agent that wraps the **Claude Agent SDK** (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`). It does NOT spawn `claude` as a subprocess. Instead, it uses the SDK's `query()` function to programmatically drive Claude Code.

**How it works**:
1. Entry point (`index.js`): Runs as `#!/usr/bin/env node`. Redirects `console.log/info/warn/debug` to stderr (stdout is reserved for ACP JSON-RPC). Calls `runAcp()`.
2. `runAcp()` creates an `AgentSideConnection` (from `@agentclientprotocol/sdk`) on stdin/stdout and registers a `ClaudeAcpAgent` handler.
3. `ClaudeAcpAgent.newSession()` calls Claude Agent SDK's `query()` to create a new Claude session.
4. `ClaudeAcpAgent.prompt()` pushes user messages into the SDK's query iterator and streams responses (tool calls, messages, thoughts) back as ACP `session/update` notifications.
5. `ClaudeAcpAgent.loadSession()` uses `getSessionMessages()` from the SDK to replay history.

**CLI args**:
- `--cli` flag: Instead of running ACP, directly imports the Claude CLI module (for auth flows like `--cli auth login --claudeai`)
- `--hide-claude-auth`: Hides Claude subscription auth option
- Settings can be provided via managed settings JSON files

**Usage in Zed** (`settings.json`):
```json
{
  "agent_servers": {
    "Claude": {
      "type": "custom",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@agentclientprotocol/claude-agent-acp"]
    }
  }
}
```

